# Runtime and backend memory lowering

GC baseline and ownership-aware backend paths.

## Contract

- Input: validated HIR; borrow facts; validated lifetime topology; selected function set; target assignment; import/export/capability plan; semantic layout identity; builder lifecycle/runtime plan
- Output: target-specific allocation, GC and ownership representations
- Decides: backend memory strategy, ownership metadata representation, fallback behaviour for already-legal topology
- Must not decide: source legality, borrow facts, region legality, target partition, or page lifecycle policy
- Invariant: every backend preserves the same shared, exclusive, copy and move semantics

## Main paths

- `src/backends/js/`
- `src/backends/wasm/`
- `src/backends/wasm/hir_to_lir/ownership.rs`
- `src/backends/wasm/lir/`
- `src/backends/wasm/runtime/`

